{"questionId":"25941","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>A farmer is placing posts at points <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>A</mtext></math>, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>B</mtext></math>, and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>C</mtext></math> in the ground to mark the boundaries of a&nbsp;triangular piece of land on his property.</p>\n<p>From point <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>A</mtext></math>, he walks due west <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>230</mn></math> metres to point <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>B</mtext></math>.<br>From point <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>B</mtext></math>, he walks <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>175</mn></math> metres on a bearing of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>063</mn><mo>°</mo></math> to reach point <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>C</mtext></math>.</p>\n<p>This is shown in the following diagram.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/93ca50c930396303a9c40bff76401c9567a2f681.png\"></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Find the distance from point <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>A</mtext></math> to point <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>C</mtext></math>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>A</mtext><mover><mtext>B</mtext><mo>^</mo></mover><mtext>C</mtext><mo>=</mo><mn>27</mn><mo>°</mo></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>attempt to substitute into cosine rule&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mn>175</mn><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><msup><mn>230</mn><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mfenced><mn>175</mn></mfenced><mfenced><mn>230</mn></mfenced><mi>cos</mi><mo> </mo><mn>27</mn><mo>°</mo></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>108</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>62308</mn><mo>…</mo></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>AC</mtext><mo>=</mo><mn>109</mn><mo> </mo><mfenced><mtext>m</mtext></mfenced></math>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[4 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"25941","referenceCode":"22M.2.SL.TZ2.7a","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Find the distance from point A to point C.","paper":"2","level":"SL","questionNumber":"a","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 4]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","SL 3.2—2d and 3d trig, sine rule, cosine rule, area"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}